This paper deals with the confluence of Constraint Handling Rules (CHR), which is a programming language paradigm falling under the category of programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses logical consistency, which is a topic in mathematical logic (cs.LO). The use of CHR in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) is also mentioned. The paper also involves the use of diagrams, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses modularity, which is a topic in software engineering (cs.SE).
